ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: CPSC532 is a course that focuses on sound-level synthesis with a musical focus for applications. I would recommend this course to other students with a music background or at least some experience playing instruments. Although sound synthesis itself doesn't necessarily require a musical background, a lot of the terminology and discussions in the lectures might be confusing for someone who is unfamiliar with various aspects of musical performance.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: I had never manipulated sound at the signal level before, so this course was very useful for me for my own experience. I expect my future research will be influenced by it.
